Masisi was in Mozambique for a one-day working visit as part of a regional diplomatic charm offensive to reassure his neighbors that relations between Gaborone and Maputo will remain intact despite the change of guard in his country early this month. 

It was Masisi's first visit to Mozambique since he took office. Masisi says Botswana considers Mozambique as a close and strategic partner in development…

